org.araneaframework.uilib.support
Class DataType

java.lang.Object
  org.araneaframework.uilib.support.DataType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable
public class DataType
extends Object
implements Serializable, Cloneable

The data definition object. Before this implementation a string representation was used instead for defining data types. Since Java 1.5 provided generics, it also became important to represent data types in way that makes good use of this new feature in Java.

The data definition basically basically supports defining classes with a single parameter (e.g. String.class, String[].class) or with a collection class to represent the first parameter as a member of the collection class (e.g. (String.class, List.class)). The latter syntax was necessary because generics does not let one define a collection class with collection item type (e.g. List<String>.class).

Since:
2.0
